  <h3>Headings</h3>
  <div class="grid-x grid-margin-x">
    <div class="cell large-6">
      <p>Heading classes are used to give elements a particular heading style, regardless of their tag. This allows for both semantic page structure and versatile design. </p>
      <p>For example, an <code>&lt;h2&gt;</code> is relatively large by default, and it may be the proper element choice, but need to be styled like a smaller <code>&lt;h4&gt;</code>.</p>
      <pre><code>&lt;h6 class="header-xxlarge">XXL Heading&lt;/h6>
&lt;h6 class="header-xlarge">XL Heading&lt;/h6>
&lt;p class="header-large">Large Heading&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="header-medium">Medium Heading&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 class="header-small">Small Heading&lt;/h1>
&lt;h1 class="header-tiny">Tiny Heading&lt;/h1></code></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="cell large-6">
      <p class="header-xxlarge">XXL Heading</p>
      <p class="header-xlarge">XL Heading</p>
      <p class="header-large">Large Heading</p>
      <p class="header-medium">Medium Heading</p>
      <p class="header-small">Small Heading</p>
      <p class="header-tiny">Tiny Heading</p>
    </div>
  </div>


