  <h3>Margins</h3>
  <div class="grid-x grid-margin-x">
    <div class="cell large-6">
      <p>The <code>.no-margin</code> class removes the margin from all 4 sides of an element with an <code>!important</code> rule. The <code>.small-margin-bottom</code> class sets the bottom margin on an element to 1/2 the <code>$global-margin</code>.</p>
      <pre><code>&lt;p>This is a regular paragraph. It has margin on its bottom side.&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="no-margin">This paragraph has no margins.&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="small-margin-bottom">This paragraph has a small margin on its bottom side.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>This is another regular paragraph.&lt;/p></code></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="cell large-6">
      <p>This is a regular paragraph. It has margin on its bottom side.</p>
      <p class="no-margin">This paragraph has no margins.</p>
      <p class="small-margin-bottom">This paragraph has a small margin on its bottom side.</p>
      <p>This is another regular paragraph.</p>
    </div>
  </div>


